completely agreed, what a plague upon the genre. It's the stupidest concept and it just won't go away: "it's scary because it's real" except you know that it's fake. I remember back when Blair Witch first came out, and I thought it was meant to be real, and that was the only thing would have been scary about it. Then I heard that it was fake and "made to look like it was real," and I was like "huh? why would you do that? what's the point?" Found footage movies are based on this really idiotic premise that "you are now seeing people in the "footage" who are acting scared. Therefore it is now your cue to be scared." Yes, thanks for letting me know. A scary film ought to scare you of its own virtue, not because there are scared people in it. And they just keep churning them out like this spreading disease, enough of this crap. At least if they gave them their own genre and it wasn't advertised as horror but rather as "found footage horror" so you'd know to avoid it.
You don't have to watch them. And I doubt many creators of found footage films are going to read that comment of yours.
